From builds at travis-ci.org  Mon Jul  4 14:02:47 2016
From: builds at travis-ci.org (Travis CI)
Date: Mon, 04 Jul 2016 13:02:47 +0000
Subject: [opam-commits] Errored: euanh/opam-repository#2 (sudo-required -
	81f0edb)
In-Reply-To: <euanh/opam-repository+142203233+errored@travis-ci.org>
Message-ID: <577a5e72722be_33fa1ba16f9f414692b@4feaf9a1-c12b-4525-819b-1a4e4c132b71.mail>

Build Update for euanh/opam-repository
-------------------------------------

Build: #2
Status: Errored

Duration: 4 minutes and 46 seconds
Commit: 81f0edb (sudo-required)
Author: Euan Harris
Message: travis.ym: Add 'sudo: required' to avoid running in a container

Without this line, Travis will run the build in a Docker container in
which sudo is not allowed.   .travis-ci-install.sh and .travis-ci.sh
both use sudo extensively.

This problem might not affect the ocaml/opam-repository Travis job as
it was created before container-based infrastructure became the default
in Travis.

Signed-off-by: Euan Harris <euan.harris at citrix.com>

View the changeset: https://github.com/euanh/opam-repository/commit/81f0edb3a4d4

View the full build log and details: https://travis-ci.org/euanh/opam-repository/builds/142203233

--

You can configure recipients for build notifications in your .travis.yml file. See https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/notifications
